  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  ASA 1-3

          -  General anaesthesia &gt;1 hour

          -  Surgery in supine position with possibility of monitoring the neuromuscular blockade
             at the thumb (n.ulnaris stimulation).

          -  Written informed content

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Neuromuscular disorders, hepatic and renal dysfunction

          -  Medication expected to interfere with the neuromuscular blocking agent

          -  Allergy to any medication used during anaesthesia

          -  Body weight less or exceeding 20% of the ideal body weight

          -  Pregnancy or breastfeeding
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
